ing merging mechanism:\nAs weakened circulation leads to accumulation of hot fluid adjacent to the hot\nsidewall, larger buoyancy forces associated with hotter fluid eventually break\nthe layer interface. Then two layers merge into a larger layer, and circulation\nestablishes again within the merged structure.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 26 Apr 2020 21:45:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-28"}
